results.name: Expansion of q^(-1/4) * eta(q) * eta(q^2) * eta(q^6) / eta(q^3) in powers of q.
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..2500
formula: G.f. is a period 1 Fourier series which satisfies f(-1 / (72 t)) = 9 (t/i) g(t) where q = exp(2 Pi i t) and g() is the g.f. for A258277.
mathematica: QP := QPochhammer; CoefficientList[Series[QP[q]*QP[q^2]*QP[q^6]/QP[q^3], {q, 0, 50}], q]] (* _G. C. Greubel_, Aug 04 2018 *)
program: (PARI) {a(n) = my(A); if( n<0, 0, A = x * O(x^n); polcoeff( eta(x + A) * eta(x^2 + A) * eta(x^6 + A) / eta(x^3 + A), n))};
